        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b><strong>Protecting Outdoor Concerts Act of 2021</strong></b></p> <p>This bill requires the Federal Aviation Administration to implement or revise its regulations to provide for temporary flight restrictions that are necessary to (1) protect persons or property on the surface or in the air, (2) maintain air safety and efficiency, or (3) prevent the unsafe congestion of aircraft in the vicinity of an outdoor concert or music festival with an attendance of not fewer than 30,000 people per day.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
